  "body": "# EIP-1559 Implementers' Call 3\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this call is for various teams/individuals working on aspects of EIP-1559 to discuss the implementation plan and next steps to move the EIP forward. \r\n\r\n-   Meeting Date/Time:  **Wednesday 24 June 2020, [19:00 UTC](https://savvytime.com/converter/utc-to-germany-berlin-united-kingdom-london-ny-new-york-city-ca-san-francisco-china-shanghai-japan-tokyo-australia-sydney-new-zealand-auckland/jun-24-2020/7pm)**\r\n-   Meeting Duration 1.5 hours\r\n-   Livestream: https://youtu.be/2qDfW83gnDA\r\n-   Meeting Link: to be posted in [#1559-fee-market channel of the Ethereum R&D Discord](https://discord.gg/B4yx9SQ) prior to call. \r\n\r\n# Agenda\r\n\r\n- Status updates from implementers\r\n- EIP-1559 & [Escalator Fees](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/pull/2593) combination/unbundling\r\n    - @MicahZoltu's [comment](https://github.com/ethereum/pm/issues/184#issuecomment-644166333)\r\n    - @barnabemonnot's [proposal](https://github.com/ethereum/rig/blob/master/eip1559/notes-call3.md)\r\n    - Derbit's [analysis of Escalator ](https://insights.deribit.com/market-research/analysis-of-eip-2593-escalator/)\r\n- Testing/Analysis\r\n    - Testnets\r\n    - Formal analysis/proof\r\n    - Simulations \r\n- [EIP-2718: Typed Transaction Envelope](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2718)\r\n- Community funding \r\n- Anything else (please leave a comment)\r\n",
